I think a struct would be the most intention revealing

  struct CStringAndUtf16Length {
     const char* string;
     uint32_t length;  // why not size_t ?
  };

Maybe even something shorter for the name like DexUtf16String.

This would have the same exact memory/performance as a pair and now people have something to grep for when they want to read the code.

